00:39:51.590 --> 00:39:53.810
he has no intention
of stepping down,

00:39:53.810 --> 00:39:55.564
as I think you pointed out.

00:39:55.564 --> 00:39:57.730
And of course, this article,
which just this morning

00:39:57.730 --> 00:39:59.910
was, of course,
talking about Navalny.

00:39:59.910 --> 00:40:03.020
And so I guess two parts of the
question from your perspective

00:40:03.020 --> 00:40:05.975
is, what is his future,
Navalny's, given

00:40:05.975 --> 00:40:08.750
how much of an uproar he's
made, particularly in the West?

00:40:08.750 --> 00:40:11.750
You know he's on "60
Minutes" a handful of times.

00:40:11.750 --> 00:40:14.360
So where is he
going, or is he not?

00:40:14.360 --> 00:40:17.240
And then where-- because a
lot of I think what he's done

00:40:17.240 --> 00:40:20.270
has been to catalyze somewhat
of the youth, and millennials,

00:40:20.270 --> 00:40:21.420
and younger people.

00:40:21.420 --> 00:40:24.530
So what role will younger people
play in the next five years?

00:40:24.530 --> 00:40:25.160
JUSTIN KOSSLYN: And
actually, it might even

00:40:25.160 --> 00:40:27.535
be worth just giving a bit of
quick context for the group

00:40:27.535 --> 00:40:29.125
on who he is and
the work he's done.

00:40:29.125 --> 00:40:31.250
IRINA BOROGRAN: Navalny is
an opposition politician

00:40:31.250 --> 00:40:36.140
who adopted a new way of
doing politics in Russia.

00:40:36.140 --> 00:40:41.360
As you know, today in Russia,
opposition politicians

00:40:41.360 --> 00:40:44.320
can now access to the media--

00:40:44.320 --> 00:40:47.660
traditional mass media, TV
channels, radio stations,

00:40:47.660 --> 00:40:50.730
and newspapers, and
they could use website--

00:40:50.730 --> 00:40:54.350
because all-- most of them are
under the Kremlin's control

00:40:54.350 --> 00:40:57.110
or under the control of
pro-Kremlin oligarchs.

00:40:57.110 --> 00:41:05.210
So he started to gain popularity
doing [INAUDIBLE] on that.

00:41:05.210 --> 00:41:10.630
He set up a special
channel on YouTube.

00:41:10.630 --> 00:41:13.730
There's another
channel on YouTube.

00:41:13.730 --> 00:41:17.600
He started-- in fact, he started
with Twitter, and YouTube

00:41:17.600 --> 00:41:22.350
channel, and his own websites.

00:41:22.350 --> 00:41:25.880
And three years ago, he
got a lot of popularity,

00:41:25.880 --> 00:41:28.860
which was even bigger.

00:41:28.860 --> 00:41:33.030
It became bigger in 2017 for
I don't know what reasons.

00:41:33.030 --> 00:41:36.845
Maybe because of
a financial crisis

00:41:36.845 --> 00:41:39.780
in Russia and bad
economic situation.

00:41:39.780 --> 00:41:44.840
Maybe because the authoritative
regime became stronger

00:41:44.840 --> 00:41:47.105
than it was, than it used to be.

00:41:47.105 --> 00:41:59.300
But his videos usually get
millions of viewers, tens,

00:41:59.300 --> 00:42:01.640
in fact, tens of
millions viewers.

00:42:01.640 --> 00:42:03.190
JUSTIN KOSSLYN: Tens of millions
of viewers on a single YouTube

00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:03.695
video.

00:42:03.695 --> 00:42:05.990
ANDREI SOLDATOV: Yeah,
so that's a great thing.

00:42:05.990 --> 00:42:10.820
And when we had the last
mass protest in Moscow,

00:42:10.820 --> 00:42:13.170
Navalny was arrested.

00:42:13.170 --> 00:42:18.110
But any case, we got--

00:42:18.110 --> 00:42:23.300
there were tens of thousands
of people on the streets.

00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:28.700
And many of them were
students, and even schoolboys

00:42:28.700 --> 00:42:29.480
and schoolgirls.

00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:32.630
That was really
unusual for Russians,

00:42:32.630 --> 00:42:37.670
because previously, we've
seen only people who's

00:42:37.670 --> 00:42:39.350
older than 20.

00:42:39.350 --> 00:42:42.680
ANDREI SOLDATOV: And maybe,
answering your question,

00:42:42.680 --> 00:42:45.670
the interesting thing now
is that previously, Navalny

00:42:45.670 --> 00:42:47.250
based all his activity online.

00:42:47.250 --> 00:42:49.390
It was always about
something online.

00:42:49.390 --> 00:42:53.760
And right now, he started
building his network offline.

00:42:53.760 --> 00:42:58.860
And surprisingly,
it's quite successful.

00:42:58.860 --> 00:43:01.530
When we got the latest
protest, Navalny

00:43:01.530 --> 00:43:04.320
tried to organize and to
enlist people in the regions.

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:06.300
And we got protests in 80 towns.

00:43:06.300 --> 00:43:07.009
Which is really--

00:43:07.009 --> 00:43:07.799
JUSTIN KOSSLYN: 80?

00:43:07.799 --> 00:43:08.640
ANDREI SOLDATOV: 80.

00:43:08.640 --> 00:43:11.964
So it's really big, because
there's a usual theory

00:43:11.964 --> 00:43:14.130
and a traditional theory
about the Russian political

00:43:14.130 --> 00:43:18.240
opposition is, yes, you
have some people voting

00:43:18.240 --> 00:43:22.620
for you in big towns, but the
rest of Russia doesn't care.

00:43:22.620 --> 00:43:24.390
And they support Putin.

00:43:24.390 --> 00:43:25.690
It's not the case now.

00:43:25.690 --> 00:43:27.690
It's a big, new development.

00:43:27.690 --> 00:43:31.170
And I think he will invest more
and more resources, and more

00:43:31.170 --> 00:43:33.480
of his time, and of
his people's time,

00:43:33.480 --> 00:43:36.150
into trying to build his
network in the regions.

00:43:36.150 --> 00:43:38.040
And as I said, that's
quite effective.

00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:39.456
It's really
interesting what might

00:43:39.456 --> 00:43:42.330
happen to him and to his
ideas, when he actually

00:43:42.330 --> 00:43:46.410
started this move, this
shift from the online world

00:43:46.410 --> 00:43:48.260
to the offline world.

00:43:48.260 --> 00:43:50.040
Of course, there
are some problems,

00:43:50.040 --> 00:43:52.560
because it's a very
traditional way

00:43:52.560 --> 00:43:54.150
of building a
political party, which

00:43:54.150 --> 00:43:56.370
means that you need
to be ready to answer

00:43:56.370 --> 00:44:00.212
some traditional questions,
like what you think

00:44:00.212 --> 00:44:02.295
about the economic situation,
political situation,

00:44:02.295 --> 00:44:04.630
I don't know,
Crimea, many things.

00:44:04.630 --> 00:44:08.010
And he is not that ready.

00:44:08.010 --> 00:44:10.090
But still, there
is some potential.

00:44:10.090 --> 00:44:11.465
IRINA BOROGRAN:
At the moment, he

