open freedom of speech more?

00:44:40.760 --> 00:44:44.220
Or is it still mostly about
just accessing the BitTorrents

00:44:44.220 --> 00:44:45.960
and pornography?

00:44:45.960 --> 00:44:46.710
This is one thing.

00:44:46.710 --> 00:44:50.940
And another thing, the topic of
our talk today, surveillance,

00:44:50.940 --> 00:44:52.590
censorship and
beyond, and I wanted

00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:54.860
to ask you a little bit
about the beyond part.

00:44:54.860 --> 00:44:58.020
Do you feel like part of the
strategy of the government when

00:44:58.020 --> 00:45:01.450
it comes to
censorship is to make

00:45:01.450 --> 00:45:05.010
the community
complacent with it,

00:45:05.010 --> 00:45:09.180
doing it through the
idea of censorship

00:45:09.180 --> 00:45:15.450
being necessary to control the
country, to fight terrorism,

00:45:15.450 --> 00:45:20.200
and to make sure Russia
grows in a stable fashion?

00:45:20.200 --> 00:45:21.750
ANDREI SOLDATOV: I will try to--

00:45:21.750 --> 00:45:23.340
it's actually the
interesting thing,

00:45:23.340 --> 00:45:26.520
but there is a way to answer
both of your questions.

00:45:26.520 --> 00:45:30.616
And one, it looks
like five years ago,

00:45:30.616 --> 00:45:31.990
when they introduced
this system,

00:45:31.990 --> 00:45:33.450
they're trying to
play some tricks,

00:45:33.450 --> 00:45:35.330
like we are protecting children.

00:45:35.330 --> 00:45:36.630
We are doing things.

00:45:36.630 --> 00:45:38.400
They're actually
just doing exactly

00:45:38.400 --> 00:45:41.224
the same thing that was first
introduced by the British.

00:45:41.224 --> 00:45:43.140
So in a way, they imitate
the British approach

00:45:43.140 --> 00:45:44.760
to internet filtering.

00:45:44.760 --> 00:45:46.670
And it looks like
some years ago,

00:45:46.670 --> 00:45:48.630
actually two years
ago, they completely

00:45:48.630 --> 00:45:50.640
abandoned all pretenses.

00:45:50.640 --> 00:45:53.400
Now, it's even not
about terrorists.

00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:54.420
It's about the West.

00:45:54.420 --> 00:45:55.590
We have the West.

00:45:55.590 --> 00:45:57.010
They are plotting against us.

00:45:57.010 --> 00:45:58.000
We need to fight back.

00:45:58.000 --> 00:45:59.400
We need to protect us.

00:45:59.400 --> 00:46:04.890
And unfortunately, this
idea is accepted by many.

00:46:04.890 --> 00:46:09.810
And even the ideas
of complete reshuffle

00:46:09.810 --> 00:46:12.210
of the infrastructure
in the country

00:46:12.210 --> 00:46:14.070
is sort of accepted by many.

00:46:14.070 --> 00:46:18.390
Because the internet is seen as
an invention of the Americans.

00:46:18.390 --> 00:46:20.130
So we need to fight back.

00:46:20.130 --> 00:46:24.590
For example, there was a crazy
story just two years ago,

00:46:24.590 --> 00:46:28.140
how the idea of
data localization

00:46:28.140 --> 00:46:29.990
was sold to Russia.

00:46:29.990 --> 00:46:33.660
Some Russian officials
sat from the stage

00:46:33.660 --> 00:46:36.920
that actually, you can see
in Crimea, some of the people

00:46:36.920 --> 00:46:39.830
are playing Warcraft.

00:46:39.830 --> 00:46:47.010
They were-- now, they are
not capable of playing,

00:46:47.010 --> 00:46:49.590
because they are cut
off by the Americans.

00:46:49.590 --> 00:46:51.390
So we need to do
something about it.

00:46:51.390 --> 00:46:54.270
And on this kind of
pretext, well, unfortunately

00:46:54.270 --> 00:46:55.440
are quite popular.

00:46:55.440 --> 00:46:57.140
And people accept this idea.

00:46:57.140 --> 00:46:59.910
IRINA BOROGRAN: And second
